cultural Sick Pay\">ASP</abbr>).</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You must be paid at least your basic pay for all normal working hours (including guaranteed overtime) for each day you&rsquo;re entitled to.</p>\n\n<h2>Away for longer than you&rsquo;re entitled to claim for</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re away for longer than the number of weeks you&rsquo;re entitled to claim for, you might be able to get <a href=\"/employment-support-allowance\" title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">Employment and Support Allowance</a> or other benefits.</p>\n\n<h2>When you&rsquo;ll be paid</h2>\n\n<p>You should be paid on your normal pay day. Your employer must pay your sick pay while you&rsquo;re off work and immediately after you come back. Each payment should be for <strong>at least</strong> the amount your employer knows you&rsquo;re entitled to (rather than guessing when you&rsquo;ll return).</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/agricultural-sick-pay/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"<p>You must have been continuously employed by the same employer for at least 52 weeks before the first day of your absence.</p>\n\n<h2>When you become entitled to Agricultural Sick Pay (<abbr title=\"Agricultural Sick Pay\">ASP</abbr>)</h2>\n\n<p>You won&rsquo;t be paid for the first 3 days off sick unless you&rsquo;re away for longer than 14 working days in total.</p>\n\n<h2>Sickness that counts for <abbr title=\"Agricultural Sick Pay\">ASP</abbr></h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your own illness, whatever caused it</li>\n  <li>your own illness or incapacity caused by pregnancy or maternity</li>\n  <li>injuries which happened at work</li>\n  <li>injuries which happened travelling to or from work</li>\n  <li>recovering from an operation caused by an illness or injury suffered at work or travelling to or from work</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re sick because of another reason, you might be entitled to <a href=\"/statutory-sick-pay-ssp\" title=\"Statutory sick pay\">Statutory Sick Pay</a>.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/agricultural-sick-pay/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":4,"title":"How to claim","body":"<p>Tell your employer about your sickness or injury and they&rsquo;ll sort out your Agricultural Sick Pay (<abbr title=\"Agricultural Sick Pay\">ASP</abbr>). If you&rsquo;re ill for longer than 8 days, you must give your employer a medical certificate (<a href=\"/taking-sick-leave\" title=\"Get a fit note\">doctor’s note</a>).</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/agricultural-sick-pay/further-information","slug":"further-information","order":5,"title":"Further information","body":"<p>If you need advice, contact the Pay and Work Rights helpline.</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/\" title=\"Online enquiry form\">Online enquiry form.</a></p>\n\n<p>If you know you&rsquo;re not being treated fairly and want to complain, use the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/complaints/\" title=\"Online complaint form\">online complaint form.</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Pay and Work Rights Helpline</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0800 917 2368</p>\n\n<p><strong>Text phone:</strong> 0800 121 4042</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:13:38+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Holidays, time off, sick leave, maternity and paternity leave","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftime-off.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes career breaks and the holiday entitlement calculator","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftime-off","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/time-off"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"ht